'''Iran Venezuela Bi-National Bank''' ({{lang-fa|بانک مشترک ایران و ونزوئلا}}, {{lang-es|Banco Binacional Irán-Venezuela}}) is an [[international financial institution]] that was founded in 2010 with an aim to develop commercial ties between [[Iran]] and [[Venezuela]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=Bailey|first=Norman A.|date=February 2012|title=Iran's Venezuelan Gateway|url=http://www.hacer.org/pdf/HHRG1122.pdf|journal=Iran Strategy Brief|issue=5}}</ref>

It started as a [[joint venture]] between two state-owned banks, [[Banco Industrial de Venezuela]] and [[Export Development Bank of Iran]] with a starting capital of $200 million offered equally by both parties.<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://financialtribune.com/articles/economy-business-and-markets/65918/5-foreign-banks-licensed-by-iran|title=5 Foreign Banks Licensed by Iran|date=2017-06-06|work=Financial Tribune|access-date=2018-08-11|language=en-US}}</ref>

In September 2013, the [[United States Department of the Treasury]] imposed sanction on the bank.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-iran-oil-sanctions/u-s-blacklists-firms-for-evading-iran-oil-sale-sanctions-idUSBRE94814Q20130509|title=U.S. blacklists firms for evading Iran oil sale sanctions|last=Gardner|first=Timothy|work=U.S.|access-date=2018-08-11|language=en-US}}</ref> In 2015, an official in the [[Central Bank of the Islamic Republic of Iran]] told press that "[the] bank is not given much freedom" and it is being managed one-sidedly by Iran, because the Venezuelan side does not participate in the general assemblies.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://en.trend.az/iran/business/2427169.html|title=Joint Iran-Venezuela bank not much of a bank: Iran|date=2015-08-25|work=Trend.Az|access-date=2018-08-11|language=en-EN}}</ref> By 2016, the Iranian side was willing to sell its share.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://financialtribune.com/articles/economy-business-and-markets/53228/iran-to-sell-shares-in-joint-bank-with-venezuela|title=Iran to Sell Shares in Joint Bank With Venezuela|date=2016-11-08|work=Financial Tribune|access-date=2018-08-11|language=en-US}}</ref>

