The [[UN]] General Assembly in December 2008 authorized the establishment of  the  '''Office of Staff Legal Assistance''' (OSLA)  to strength "professional legal assistance for staff" to succeed the Panel of Counsel.<ref name="62/228">{{cite web|last1=UN GA|title=62/228. Administration of justice at the United Nations|url=https://www.un.org/Depts/DGACM/A.Res.62.228.pdf|publisher=General Assembly|accessdate=1 April 2015|language=English|date=6 February 2008}}</ref>{{rp|para(S) 12–13 }}  OSLA has offices  in New York, Addis Ababa, Beirut, Geneva and Nairobi.<ref name="62/228">{{cite web|last1=UN GA|title=62/228. Administration of justice at the United Nations|url=https://www.un.org/Depts/DGACM/A.Res.62.228.pdf|publisher=General Assembly|accessdate=1 April 2015|language=English|date=6 February 2008}}</ref>{{rp|para 14}}

== OSLA Staff==
OSLA has  permanent  staff  consisting of  10: Chief of Unit (P-5), one Legal Officer (P3), one Legal Officer (P-2) and three Legal Assistants (General Service) in New York, and one Legal Officer(P-3) each in Addis Ababa, Beirut, Geneva and Nairobi.<ref name="62/228">{{cite web|last1=UN GA|title=62/228. Administration of justice at the United Nations|url=https://www.un.org/Depts/DGACM/A.Res.62.228.pdf|publisher=General Assembly|accessdate=1 April 2015|language=English|date=6 February 2008}}</ref>{{rp|para 14}}  In addition  it employs lawyers paid for by  contributions by staff members.  The  OSLA staff  is expected to  regulate  the "activity of internal and external individuals providing legal assistance to staff to ensure their independence and impartiality" <ref name="62/228">{{cite web|last1=UN GA|title=62/228. Administration of justice at the United Nations|url=https://www.un.org/Depts/DGACM/A.Res.62.228.pdf|publisher=General Assembly|accessdate=1 April 2015|language=English|date=6 February 2008}}</ref>{{rp|para(S) 17}} <ref name="activity report 2013">{{cite web|title=Seventh activity report Office of Administration of Justice 1 January to 31 December 2013|url=https://www.un.org/en/oaj/unjs/pdf/Seventh_activity_report_OAJ.pdf|publisher=Office of Administration of Justice|accessdate=1 April 2015|pages=12–17|date=2014}}</ref> {{rp|para 55}}

== Responsibilities==
OSLA  is expected to   provide   legal assistance to staff, including summary legal advice; advice and representation during informal dispute resolution including formal mediation; assistance with the management evaluation review and during the disciplinary process; and representation of staff before the Dispute and Appeals Tribunals.<ref name="activity report 2013">{{cite web|title=Seventh activity report Office of Administration of Justice 1 January to 31 December 2013|url=https://www.un.org/en/oaj/unjs/pdf/Seventh_activity_report_OAJ.pdf|publisher=Office of Administration of Justice|accessdate=1 April 2015|pages=12–17|date=2014}}</ref> {{rp|para 60}}

== Cases  by OSLA ==

===UNDT-UNAT===
During 2013, OSLA represented staff members in the UNDT in  71, and   34  out of the 125 cases of appeal  judged by UNAT.<ref name="activity report 2013">{{cite web|title=Seventh activity report Office of Administration of Justice 1 January to 31 December 2013|url=https://www.un.org/en/oaj/unjs/pdf/Seventh_activity_report_OAJ.pdf|publisher=Office of Administration of Justice|accessdate=1 April 2015|pages=12–17|date=2014}}</ref> {{rp|para 60}}

===Cases in UNDT handled by OSLA by Country===
The highest number of cases by nationality that OSLA represented  in 2013 were: [[US]]  41; [[Russian federation]] 29;  [[Kenya]] 19: [[United Kingdom]] 12;  [[France]] 11; [[Liberia]] 13; [[Germany]] and [[China]] 10 each. Amongst the larger countries the fewest cases overseen by OSLA were  from India  and Brazil had just 1.<ref name="activity report 2013">{{cite web|title=Seventh activity report Office of Administration of Justice 1 January to 31 December 2013|url=https://www.un.org/en/oaj/unjs/pdf/Seventh_activity_report_OAJ.pdf|publisher=Office of Administration of Justice|accessdate=1 April 2015|pages=12–17|date=2014}}</ref> {{rp| AppendixII page 26 }}

===Cases by Gender===
In 2013,  OSLA handled  448 cases from male staff members and 314 from female staff members, about 41 and 59 percent respectively.<ref name="activity report 2013">{{cite web|title=Seventh activity report Office of Administration of Justice 1 January to 31 December 2013|url=https://www.un.org/en/oaj/unjs/pdf/Seventh_activity_report_OAJ.pdf|publisher=Office of Administration of Justice|accessdate=1 April 2015|pages=12–17|date=2014}}</ref> {{rp|para 67}}

